Architecture Document with RoadMap (e.g. aim of HBASE-4002?)
Marriage != integration
What are the options?
Solr/ElasticSearch as “helper” or more?
Extend Lucene by implementing own Directory class, or implement new IndexReader Òand IndexWriter (a-la-Lucandra)? (probably the second option)
Try to let Lucene evolve? (Extensions vs Interfaces)
http://lucene.grantingersoll.com/2008/03/28/why-lucene-isnt-that-good-javalobby/   http://java.dzone.com/news/why-lucene-isnt-good?page=0%2C1  
Still no interface https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/lucene/dev/trunk/lucene/src/java/org/apache/lucene/index/IndexWriter.java 
See also for classes vs interfaces http://www.symphonious.net/2011/06/18/the-single-implementation-fallacy/ 
Do we rely on HBase Coprocessors? https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2000
Do we use distributed memory cache? (Hazelcast...)
Are there JSON, Avro... requirements?
Need for special queries? (Spatial with geohash...)
 List of existing JIRA to implement + Definition of additional JIRA
